        "docId": "a2659ede-3d1e-440e-9b33-6ad9dbd0fc34",
        "type": "lessons learned",
        "title": "Complicated pumping schedule for 7\" liner job",
        "description": "Pumped 5 different fluids in conjunction with 7\" cementing job: \n- 1.18 sg OBM \n- Base oil\n- Spacer\n- 1.06 sg filtered brine\n- 1.18 sg viscosified brine\n\nObserved 3 different fluids in bottom of liner when performing USIT/CBL. \nIntervals: \n1: TOL - 3804 m \n2: 3804 m - 3845 m \n3: 3845 m - 4054 m",
        "cause": "Possible to simplify pumping schedule??",
